255
00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:33.791
Oh, well, that's great.

256
00:15:33.875 --> 00:15:35.125
Where are your hat and scarf?

257
00:15:35.208 --> 00:15:36.708
Uh, I don't know.

258
00:15:37.916 --> 00:15:40.791
I guess I must've
dropped them in the snow.

259
00:15:40.875 --> 00:15:43.833
Oh, Greg, your Aunt
Lydia made those for you.

260
00:15:43.916 --> 00:15:46.583
Well, it would break her heart
if she found out you lost them.

261
00:15:46.666 --> 00:15:50.166
I'm sure they'll turn up when
the snow melts in the spring.

262
00:15:50.250 --> 00:15:52.666
Oh, someone will probably
find them before then.

263
00:15:52.750 --> 00:15:56.291
And luckily for you, Aunt Lydia stitched
your name on the inside of your hat.

264
00:15:56.375 --> 00:15:58.541
Wait. My-My name's in there?

265
00:15:58.625 --> 00:15:59.875
First and last.

266
00:15:59.958 --> 00:16:04.333
So don't worry, whoever finds your things
won't have any trouble tracking you down.

267
00:16:04.416 --> 00:16:05.458
Greg?

268
00:16:05.541 --> 00:16:06.625
- Uh…
- Are you okay?

269
00:16:06.708 --> 00:16:09.833
Yeah. I think I just need to
get warmed up by the fire.

270
00:16:09.916 --> 00:16:12.083
Oh, there'll be plenty of
time for that later on.

271
00:16:12.166 --> 00:16:16.000
Right now, we're going on
a holiday family outing.

272
00:16:16.083 --> 00:16:19.500
But... Mom, I can't
go back out there.

273
00:16:19.583 --> 00:16:22.083
You can borrow your
father's old hat and scarf.

274
00:16:22.166 --> 00:16:23.916
I don't want you
catching a cold.

275
00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:27.500
Guys, let's go!
Holiday lights time!

276
00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:30.500
- I'll be up in a sec!
- Do I have to go?

277
00:16:38.166 --> 00:16:40.583
After that I get
to have the elf.

278
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:43.500
♪ You know Dasher and
Dancer Prancer and Vixen ♪

279
00:16:43.583 --> 00:16:46.416
♪ Comet and Cupid and
