What's that? ♪

281
00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:49.684
- ♪ The most famous reindeer of all? ♪
- Look.

282
00:16:49.708 --> 00:16:50.541
Manny.

283
00:16:50.625 --> 00:16:51.625
♪ Come on ♪

284
00:16:53.750 --> 00:16:54.916
Guys.

285
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:58.666
Am I the only one with any
Christmas spirit in this family?

286
00:16:58.750 --> 00:17:02.250
I'm sorry. I'm just not in the mood
for Christmas carols right now.

287
00:17:02.833 --> 00:17:03.934
Can we go back home now? I...

288
00:17:03.958 --> 00:17:06.083
We're not cutting this
drive short, Greg.

289
00:17:06.166 --> 00:17:08.250
It is our family tradition.

290
00:17:08.333 --> 00:17:10.041
Whoo-hoo.

291
00:17:10.125 --> 00:17:11.541
Oh, Rodrick.

292
00:17:13.125 --> 00:17:15.017
Starting late Thursday night,

293
00:17:15.041 --> 00:17:17.291
we're expecting a total
winter whiteout of mass...

294
00:17:17.375 --> 00:17:18.708
Come on, Frank.

295
00:17:18.791 --> 00:17:20.916
Could you please stop
obsessing over the weather?

296
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:23.666
They're saying this could
be the storm of the century.

297
00:17:23.750 --> 00:17:25.166
I just wanna be prepared.

298
00:17:25.250 --> 00:17:27.958
Those weather people are
always hyping storms.

299
00:17:28.041 --> 00:17:29.875
It's what keeps
them in business.

300
00:17:30.833 --> 00:17:32.250
Oh, honey.

301
00:17:32.333 --> 00:17:35.208
We gotta remember to donate a few
things for the toy drive this year.

302
00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.916
- The toy drive?
- Yes, Greg.

303
00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:40.958
That drop box is where everyone leaves
their spare toys for needy kids.

304
00:17:41.041 --> 00:17:43.666
The toys get picked
up on Christmas Eve.

305
00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:45.166
Drop box?

306
00:17:46.583 --> 00:17:47.791
What is it gonna be?

307
00:17:49.291 --> 00:17:54.583
Cold ears? Or
life behind bars?

308
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:59.333
Mm-hmm.

309
00:18:01.166 --> 00:18:02.875
- Attention, all units.
- Uh…

310
00:18:02.958 --> 00:18:04.892
Possible suspects sighted
westbound on Surrey Street.

311
00:18:04.916 --> 00:18:06.041
Seven Adam 15.

312
00:18:06.125 --> 00:18:07.642
Vehicle has been
dispatched to the scene.

313
00:18:07.666 --> 00:18:10.458
Suspect is wanted in connection
with an incident of vandalism.

314
00:18:18.041 --> 00:18:19.208
Is that supposed to be us?

315
00:18:19.291 --> 00:18:22.291
Rowley, we gotta get rid of these
things before someone sees them.

316
00:18:30.333 --> 00:18:31.333
Greg.

317
00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:35.833
There's so many of them. What
if we don't get them all?

318
00:18:36.458 --> 00:18:38.708
We cannot afford to let
that happen, Rowley.

319
00:18:41.458 --> 00:18:43.138
What if someone in the
neighborhood saw us?

320
00:18:44.208 --> 00:18:46.625
Well, hello, Greg Heffley.

321
00:18:46.708 --> 00:18:49.916
Wanna finish building me?

322
00:18:50.583 --> 00:18:53.125
No, thanks, Fregley.

323
00:18:53.208 --> 00:18:55.125
I've been out here
since yesterday.

324
00:18:55.208 --> 00:18:58.458
I can't feel any
of my extremities.

325
00:18:59.833 --> 00:19:01.541
How'd he get in there?

326
00:19:01.625 --> 00:19:03.166
Keep walking.

327
00:19:03.250 --> 00:19:05.208
Do not make eye contact.

328
00:19:05.291 --> 00:19:09.208
I think my freckles
might have frostbite.

329
00:19:09.833 --> 00:19:12.375
I don't feel good about
being so close to my house.

330
00:19:13.166 --> 00:19:15.666
Hey, maybe I can crash at
your place for a few days

331
00:19:15.750 --> 00:19:18.166
and wait for this whole
thing to blow over.

332
00:19:18.250 --> 00:19:21.125
But you're banned from
sleeping over at my house.

333
00:19:21.208 --> 00:19:23.166
Remember the thing with
the chocolate pudding?

334
00:19:25.833 --> 00:19:27.666
What? Come on, Rowley.

335
00:19:27.750 --> 00:19:30.375
Your dad's probably forgotten
all about that by now.

336
00:19:30.458 --> 00:19:32.625
No.

337
00:19:32.708 --> 00:19:36.375
Look, Rowley, you do not know
what it's like at my house.

338
00:19:36.458 --> 00:19:39.458
I've got, like, five pairs of
eyes watching my every move.

339
00:19:39.541 --> 00:19:40.541
Five?

340
00:19:40.625 --> 00:19:44.125
But there's only four other
people in your family.

341
00:19:44.208 --> 00:19:47.375
Well, at least that's
what it feels like.

342
00:19:47.458 --> 00:19:49.125
But you said we
don't need to worry,

343
00:19:49.208 --> 00:19:51.708
'cause we got rid of our
clothes in that dumpster, right?

344
00:19:51.791 --> 00:19:55.208
- Oh. Yeah, about that.
- What?

345
00:19:55.875 --> 00:20:00.208
Yeah, it turns out the dumpster
is actually a toy donation bin.

346
00:20:00.958 --> 00:20:02.208
It's what?

347
00:20:02.291 --> 00:20:04.791
That means someone's
gonna find our clothes.

348
00:20:04.875 --> 00:20:06.791
This is bad. This is ba...

349
00:20:06.875 --> 00:20:08.500
Calm down.

350
00:20:08.583 --> 00:20:12.166
I mean, it's not like our names
are written inside of them, right?

351
00:20:12.250 --> 00:20:16.458
But what if they find hair in
our hats and test it for DNA?

352
00:20:16.541 --> 00:20:18.125
Wow. Wow, Rowley.

353
00:20:18.208 --> 00:20:20.208
You watch way too
much television.

354
00:20:20.291 --> 00:20:22.666
Look, we'll get our clothes
back just to be safe.

355
00:20:22.750 --> 00:20:24.916
- Okay?
- Maybe we should just turn ourselves in.

356
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:26.333
I can't live like this.

357
00:20:26.416 --> 00:20:28.375
Breathe, Rowley.

358
00:20:28.458 --> 00:20:31.250
I got everything under
control. Here's the plan.

359
00:20:32.416 --> 00:20:35.208
We'll set our alarms, so we wake
up first thing in the morning.

360
00:20:35.291 --> 00:20:38.583
Then we'll head downtown and
grab our stuff out of that bin.

361
00:20:38.666 --> 00:20:42.291
And we get rid of it
for real this time.

362
00:20:42.375 --> 00:20:44.791
When that's done,
we are home free.

363
00:20:45.708 --> 00:20:47.916
Why don't we just do it now?

364
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:51.250
My mom's making us build a
gingerbread house tonight,

365
00:20:51.333 --> 00:20:52.875
and I can't get out of it.

366
00:20:52.958 --> 00:20:56.666
I don't know. This plan
seems kind of risky.

367
00:20:56.750 --> 00:20:58.916
Look, you gotta
trust me, Rowley.

368
00:20:59.500 --> 00:21:01.083
Have I ever steered you wrong?

369
00:21:02.458 --> 00:21:03.541
A bunch of times.

370
00:21:05.958 --> 00:21:07.791
You gotta believe, Rowley.

371
00:21:07.875 --> 00:21:10.125
Come on. It's Christmastime.

372
00:21:11.708 --> 00:21:12.708
Uh…

373
00:21:26.458 --> 00:21:28.166
…between ten below zero

374
00:21:28.250 --> 00:21:30.083
and 24 below zero.

375
00:21:30.166 --> 00:21:33.833
A snow emergency is in effect, with
levels reaching well above five feet.

376
00:21:33.916 --> 00:21:37.083
- Frank, can you please...
- Can't talk! Concentrating.

377
00:21:37.166 --> 00:21:38.666
Come on. Why won't this thing...

378
00:21:38.750 --> 00:21:41.083
Would you please stop
obsessing about this storm?

379
00:21:42.083 --> 00:21:45.583
You're missing out on an authentic
holiday moment with your family.

380
00:21:45.666 --> 00:21:46.791
Manny.

381
00:21:47.791 --> 00:21:50.708
Mom, how come I have to be
here, but Rodrick doesn't?

382
00:21:50.791 --> 00:21:54.208
Well, I'd love for him to be here,
but I have no idea where he is.

383
00:21:55.250 --> 00:21:56.750
It's like herding cats to get

384
00:21:56.833 --> 00:21:59.083
everyone in this
family in one place.

385
00:21:59.166 --> 00:22:01.500
Hey, look what I just found.

386
00:22:03.625 --> 00:22:05.375
Oh, I heard about that.

387
00:22:06.500 --> 00:22:09.708
Can you believe that that snowplow
assault happened on our street?

388
00:22:09.791 --> 00:22:11.333
You know, I'll bet
the guys behind it

389
00:22:11.416 --> 00:22:13.458
were a couple of those
rotten Whirley Street kids.

390
00:22:13.541 --> 00:22:16.375
They're always coming into our
neighborhood and stirring up trouble.

391
00:22:16.458 --> 00:22:18.767
Yeah, but the Whirley Street kids
wouldn't do something so bold

392
00:22:18.791 --> 00:22:20.458
in broad daylight.

393
00:22:20.541 --> 00:22:24.750
No, no. These two look
like hardened criminals.

394
00:22:24.833 --> 00:22:26.833
I could take 'em.

395
00:22:26.916 --> 00:22:29.041
Ooh, it looks like
they're offering a reward

396
00:22:29.125 --> 00:22:31.083
for more information that
leads to their capture.

397
00:22:31.166 --> 00:22:33.750
Yep. And I'm gonna claim it.

398
00:22:33.833 --> 00:22:36.083
It's how I'm paying for
your Christmas gifts.

399
00:22:36.166 --> 00:22:39.333
Mom? Mom? Can I
please be excused?

400
00:22:39.416 --> 00:22:40.833
Absolutely not, Greg.

401
00:22:40.916 --> 00:22:45.166
We are going to finish this
gingerbread house together as a family.

402
00:22:45.250 --> 00:22:46.750
Huh?

403
00:22:50.666 --> 00:22:52.500
- Bubby!
- Ugh!

404
00:22:52.583 --> 00:22:55.000
Okay… …let's pivot.

405
00:22:55.083 --> 00:22:58.250
Frank, uh, you go get those
toys that we're gonna donate.

406
00:22:58.333 --> 00:23:01.291
And, Greg... Ooh, run upstairs
and get the wrapping paper

407
00:23:01.375 --> 00:23:02.958
from the linen closet.

408
00:23:03.041 --> 00:23:06.166
This one here looks
kind of familiar.

409
00:23:07.166 --> 00:23:08.500
Hmm.

410
00:23:08.583 --> 00:23:09.750
Uh…

411
00:23:11.500 --> 00:23:13.708
Hmm.

412
00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:18.666
Mom, which one's the
linen closet again?

413
00:23:18.750 --> 00:23:20.583
The one where we
keep the towels.

414
00:23:21.375 --> 00:23:22.375
Got it.

415
00:23:29.583 --> 00:23:30.875
What?

416
00:23:37.375 --> 00:23:38.958
No way.

417
00:23:39.041 --> 00:23:41.541
I couldn't believe my eyes.

418
00:23:41.625 --> 00:23:46.458
The one thing I wanted was right
there in one glorious, beautiful...

419
00:23:46.541 --> 00:23:49.708
Oh, Greg, and grab the tape
while you're up there too.

420
00:23:49.791 --> 00:23:51.625
Of course, Mother. I'm coming.

421
00:23:59.041 --> 00:24:00.416
Yes!

422
00:24:06.416 --> 00:24:09.583
Okay. I got three varieties
of paper and clear tape.

423
00:24:10.291 --> 00:24:11.833
You need anything else?

424
00:24:11.916 --> 00:24:15.166
Oh, well, aren't
you being helpful?

425
00:24:15.250 --> 00:24:17.333
I guess I got the
Christmas spirit.

426
00:24:17.416 --> 00:24:21.458
Well, if you keep this up, I bet Santa
will have something extra special for you

427
00:24:21.541 --> 00:24:22.791
on Christmas morning.

428
00:24:22.875 --> 00:24:25.375
You know, I don't
really care what I get.

429
00:24:25.458 --> 00:24:27.916
I'm just trying to be the
best Greg Heffley I could be.

430
00:24:28.541 --> 00:24:30.791
Oh, aren't you a doll?

431
00:24:32.208 --> 00:24:34.708
Why don't you help me
wrap these used toys?

432
00:24:34.791 --> 00:24:36.041
Sure thing, Mom.

433
00:24:37.333 --> 00:24:39.291
After the thing that
happened with the snowplow,

434
00:24:39.375 --> 00:24:41.125
I figured my holidays were sunk,

435
00:24:41.208 --> 00:24:44.750
but everything changed for me
tonight when I found that gift.

436
00:24:44.833 --> 00:24:48.250
It just proves that sometimes,
good things happen to good people.

437
00:24:48.333 --> 00:24:51.625
Now, all I need to do is grab that
stuff out of the bin tomorrow,

438
00:24:51.708 --> 00:24:54.291
and it'll be smooth
sailing to Christmas.

439
00:24:54.375 --> 00:24:56.375
You know that poem about
children going to bed

440
00:24:56.458 --> 00:24:58.875
with visions of sugarplums
dancing in their heads?

441
00:24:59.541 --> 00:25:03.791
Well, tonight I'll be dreaming of
something way better than candy.

442
00:25:25.083 --> 00:25:26.083
What the heck?

443
00:25:26.833 --> 00:25:27.916
What the heck?

444
00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:30.101
The governor has declared
a weather emergency…

445
00:25:30.125 --> 00:25:32.791
- What the heck?
- Well, look who came to join us.

446
00:25:32.875 --> 00:25:34.083
It's snowing!

447
00:25:34.166 --> 00:25:36.351
I guess the weather people are
right every once in a while.

448
00:25:36.375 --> 00:25:37.916
My alarm didn't go off.

449
00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:40.083
I set it for later,
so you could sleep in.

450
00:25:40.166 --> 00:25:42.083
That's the best thing
about a snow day.

451
00:25:42.166 --> 00:25:44.333
More like a snow week.

452
00:25:44.416 --> 00:25:47.250
This storm's supposed to keep
going strong through Christmas Eve.

453
00:25:47.333 --> 00:25:49.083
A whole week?

454
00:25:49.166 --> 00:25:51.750
Uh, uh, I can't be
stuck inside right now.

455
00:25:51.833 --> 00:25:53.583
I've got... I've got
things I gotta do.

456
00:25:53.666 --> 00:25:55.333
Greg, where on
Earth are you going?

457
00:25:55.416 --> 00:25:57.500
I'm going to hang
out at Rowley's.

458
00:25:57.583 --> 00:25:59.166
In your pajamas?

459
00:25:59.250 --> 00:26:01.791
Honey, it's not safe to
be outside right now.

460
00:26:01.875 --> 00:26:03.958
Mom, it's just a dusting.

461
00:26:04.041 --> 00:26:06.625
I'll be back in a few...

462
00:26:08.875 --> 00:26:10.500
Greg.

463
00:26:10.583 --> 00:26:11.833
Bubby frozen.

464
00:26:14.250 --> 00:26:17.250
